data.description: Stunning home in the desirable Blanco Vista neighborhood offers an open floor plan with custom-grade character throughout. Boasting 4 bedrooms, 3.5 bathrooms, and a 3-car garage on a spacious .34-acre corner lot with no rear neighbors, it's a perfect blend of privacy and parking space. Feels like it’s sitting on its own block. The eye-catching 8-foot mahogany entry door adds to its curb appeal. Inside, you'll find impressive features like high ceilings, wooden floors, and abundant natural light. The kitchen shines with wood beams, a split-level brick island, pendant lighting, granite countertops, 42" cabinets, and top-notch stainless steel appliances including a cooktop and built-in dual ovens. The main floor's oversized master bedroom comes with a walk-in closet with built in shelves, luxurious walk-in shower and seat, garden tub, and dual sinks. The upper level features a large game room with an arched Romeo and Juliet balcony, spacious bedrooms, and a full bath with a Jack and Jill bathroom. The home also includes a covered porch, back patio, and a sizable backyard with potential for a pool or storage building. Conveniently located near amenities, major stores, dining, entertainment, hike and bike trails, this home offers quick access to IH35, and is only 5 miles from Texas State University. Don't miss the chance to see this captivating home in person!
